Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with speech recognition and retrieval tasks, which are part of natural language processing. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is also a likely category as the paper deals with acoustic sequences and embeddings. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper uses deep bidirectional LSTM models for learning embeddings. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with developing neural embeddings for speech recognition and retrieval tasks. 
- cs.SI (Signal Processing) is another possible category as the paper deals with processing acoustic signals to generate embeddings.
